						<summary>

						<p>Pillar (third) in the <hi rend="italic">mukha-maṇḍapa</hi> of the Talakaṇṭamma shrine.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Sādhāraṇa, Magha śu. 7, Thursday.</hi> However, on the basis of palaeography it may be assigned to the 14th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It registers the apportionment of <hi rend="italic">vṛittis</hi> of the temple land between the two sons of a certain Jīya.</p>						

						<p>[<hi rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi> No. 333].</p>						

						</summary>
